        ?><varlistentry><term>Returns:</term><listitem><para>The result of this function must be assigned to a variable of type  <computeroutput><link linkend="boost.contract.check">boost::contract::check</link></computeroutput> declared explicitly (i.e., without using C++11 <computeroutput>auto</computeroutput> declarations) and locally just before the code of the function body (otherwise this library will generate a run-time error, see <computeroutput><link linkend="BOOST_CO_idm45125848615536">BOOST_CONTRACT_ON_MISSING_CHECK_DECL</link></computeroutput>). </para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsect1></refentry>
